Full job descriptionFull job description
Infosys is seeking a Test Analyst. As a Test Analyst, you will act as a validation and quality assurance expert and review the functionality of existing systems. You will conduct requirement analysis, define test strategy & design and lead execution to guarantee superior outcomes. You will have the opportunity to collaborate with some of the best talent in the industry to create innovative high quality and defect-free solutions to meet our clients’ business needs. You will be part of a learning culture, where teamwork and collaboration are encouraged, excellence is rewarded, and diversity is respected and valued.

Required Qualifications

At least 2 years of Information Technology experience
Candidate must be located within commuting distance of Mississauga/Toronto, ON or be willing to relocate one of these areas.
Bachelor’s degree or foreign equivalent required from an accredited institution. Will also consider three years of progressive experience in the specialty in lieu of every year of education.
Candidates authorized to work for any employer in Canada without employer-based visa sponsorship are welcome to apply. Infosys is unable to provide immigration sponsorship for this role at this time.
Technical and Professional Requirements:
Minimum 4 years of experience in software test automation
Experience of data migration and ETL testing, ensuring data integrity and completeness in GCP and/or Azure cloud environments.
Utilize advanced SQL skills for data validation, transformation, and troubleshooting.
Develop and maintain automated test scripts using open-source toolkits such as Python and/or Java.
Implement test strategy, approach aligned with project goals.
Collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams, demonstrating leadership in driving data quality assurance
Experience in Power BI, Qlik testing experience is preferred

Responsibilities:
Your primary role would be to interface with the client stakeholders and delivery quality assurance via automated tests, defects identification and retest, daily test status reporting.
You will be responsible for creation and/or enhancement of test automation frameworks.
You will participate in project estimations, provide inputs and participate in automation code reviews and show & tell to customers.
You will ensure continuous knowledge/lean documentation management of the artifacts being built and adherence to the client’s guidelines and processes.
You would be a key contributor to building efficient programs/ systems and if you think you fit right in to help our clients navigate their next in their digital transformation journey, this is the place for you !

Additional preferred skills:
Knowledge of more than one automation scripting technologies and automation tools.
Analytical abilities, Strong Technical Skills, Good communication skills
Awareness of latest technologies and trends
Good problem solving, analytical and debugging skills
About the Role

We are seeking a Senior Automation Engineer with strong expertise in backend API automation, particularly in Java, REST Assured, and cloud-based testing tools. The ideal candidate will play a key role in designing and implementing robust automation frameworks, ensuring high-quality API validation, and collaborating closely with development and QA teams to drive excellence across our software delivery lifecycle.

Responsibilities

Design, develop, and maintain automation frameworks for backend API testing using Java and Selenium.
Build and execute comprehensive API test cases, covering functional, regression, and performance aspects.
Utilize tools like Jira to manage test cases, track defects, and ensure traceability.
Integrate API automation into CI/CD pipelines for seamless execution.
Work with AWS services to validate APIs in cloud-native environments.
Collaborate with developers, product managers, and QA to define automation strategies and improve product quality.
Mentor junior team members in automation best practices.
Provide detailed reporting and analysis of test execution results, ensuring issues are identified and resolved quickly.
Must-Have Skills

6+ years of experience in automation engineering, with a focus on API testing.
Strong hands-on experience in Java and Selenium framework.
Proficiency in API testing methodologies and validation strategies
Expertise with Jira for defect tracking and test management.
Working knowledge of AWS services related to API hosting, monitoring, or testing.
Solid understanding of CI/CD pipelines and integrating automated tests.
Strong debugging and problem-solving skills.
Nice-to-Have Skills

Familiarity with additional test automation frameworks (e.g., Postman/Newman, Karate).
Exposure to performance testing of APIs.
with containerized environments (Docker/Kubernetes).
